{"id":14880727,"mediaExerciseId":"09d28915-dd1f-4c1e-ad96-3c3b1352145b","exerciseName":"13","chapterName":"1","chapterTitle":"Introduction To Corporate Finance","groupId":612257,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":18,"solutions":[{"id":5890255,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine if the goal of maximizing the value of the stock be different if we were thinking about financial management in a foreign country.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/7b13baf054ad5aca05d70f292e7abba7/2a663702f84bf67faf8e542e3d472da5/lateximg_large.png","width":1002},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/7b13baf054ad5aca05d70f292e7abba7/2a663702f84bf67faf8e542e3d472da5/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financial management.\n\n**Financial management** is a strategic planning, organizing, directing, and controlling of a company's finances.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/7b13baf054ad5aca05d70f292e7abba7/185545b3448734394cf44f6b40990330/lateximg_large.png","width":993},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/7b13baf054ad5aca05d70f292e7abba7/185545b3448734394cf44f6b40990330/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Our goal of maximizing the value of the stock will still be the same if we were thinking about financial management in a foreign country. There will just be adjustments in the course of action in achieving the goal because of different social, political, and economic climates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/7b13baf054ad5aca05d70f292e7abba7/922a2a6cce0dea6537661e4f26cb9dcd/lateximg_large.png","width":1000},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/15/7b13baf054ad5aca05d70f292e7abba7/922a2a6cce0dea6537661e4f26cb9dcd/lateximg.png","width":501}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a4c4c53b-a931-4710-8bcd-afab01945893","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3},{"id":6375273,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"To complete this task, we must determine whether or not maximizing shares value would be different in a foreign country.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Maximizing the value of a company's stock is one important component in achieving value maximization goals. When it comes to running a company, the executive board members and high-level managers are often focused on increasing  \"shareholder value\", which refers to the return on investment shareholders get. Increasing the price of a stock over time and the amount of dividends paid out may help a company maximize the value it provides to shareholders. The emphasis that businesses place on maximizing shareholder value is a practice that is often criticized since it may result in a number of undesirable outcomes.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The goal of financial management in a foreign nation does not vary from that of financial management in a local country, since the ultimate objective of all enterprises is to maximize profits regardless of the country in which they operate. However, the strategy used in order to maximize the value of the stock varies from country to country due to the fact that each nation's social and political circumstances are unique.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"4a01cdc3-50a5-482e-986d-a50d40476745","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880728,"exerciseName":"14","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f07b665b-ac04-41a6-8702-0595e9a5f7bf","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-14-f07b665b-ac04-41a6-8702-0595e9a5f7bf"},{"id":14880729,"exerciseName":"15","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"d7cff783-ceef-485f-8fa0-d2461aed99f8","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-15-d7cff783-ceef-485f-8fa0-d2461aed99f8"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880726,"exerciseName":"12","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6e345553-f9b0-4aa1-9e18-7a3361e86f3e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-12-6e345553-f9b0-4aa1-9e18-7a3361e86f3e"},{"id":14880725,"exerciseName":"11","page":18,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"17428dcb-16fa-465c-acb1-34322542291c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-11-17428dcb-16fa-465c-acb1-34322542291c"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-critical-thinking-questions-13-09d28915-dd1f-4c1e-ad96-3c3b1352145b"}